  "doc_id": "35328",
  "text": "It follows that minimizing σ max (K) results in a larger abscissa. Thus, it is worth searching for a starting point K (0) that maximizes the abscissa α. This can be done efficiently by running a binary search on the abscissa and using the RS algorithm as an oracle. Note that RS CPU time appearing in the third column of Table 1 relates to running the RS algorithm for known optimal value of the abscissa. The RS algorithm is sufficiently fast also for this purpose, but other methods such as the HIFOO algorithm (see [CITATION_1] ) can be applied for this purpose as well.",
  "correct_citation": {
